observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the LCE direct the:
(a) GSO to prioritize the preparation and/or reconstruction of property records and registries; and
(b) Municipal Inventory Committee to;
i. attach property tags and property numbers to each PPE item adopting the prescribed numbering system of COA Circular No. 2020-006;
ii assign value to the PPE found at station through application of the options presented in the same Circular; and
iii perform the mandated procedures for the disposal of the identified unserviceable properties.

We recommended that the LCE:
(a) continue supporting the national government’s goals through diligent implementation of programs using the fund transferred by national agencies;
(b) instruct the Municipal Accountant to;
i. reclassify funds held in trust from the Due to NGAs and Due to LGUs account to the proper Trust Liability account; and
ii. determine the nature of the dormant balances in the Due to NGAs and Due to LGUs accounts, and subsequently request write-off if warranted.

We recommended that the LCE instruct the MENRO to:
(a) regularly assess, monitor, and update, as warranted, the SWMP projections on waste and revenue generation;
(b) encourage stakeholders to actively participate in IEC minimizing waste generation through regular IEC activities;
(c) provide enough storage area in the MRF for the by-products of their waste diversion activities; and
(d) have a concrete plan for the sale or disposition of the products of their waste diversion activities.

We recommended that the LCE:
(a) direct the BPLO to;
i. ensure strict enforcement of the submission of ITRs and related documents, as applicable;
ii. revisit the assessment made on the identified taxpayers, and collect the outstanding business tax, as warranted;
iii. henceforth, see to it that all establishments doing business in the Municipality have valid business permits; and
(b) Municipal Treasurer to;
i. conduct regular examination of books of accounts of businesses; and
ii. ensure diligent collection of business taxes from all eligible entities.

We recommended that the LCE instruct the GAD FP to:
(a) carefully plan the corresponding budget allocations of GAD PPAs by preparing project breakdown of expenses before the approval of the plan and budget;
(b) create a multi-year GAD Agenda as basis for the annual GAD Plans and Budget by using the templates provided in PCW Memorandum Circular No. 2018-04 dated September 19, 2018;
(c) conduct a review after three years and an end-term evaluation to reflect on the status of accomplishment, variances, and overall assessment of the implementation of the GAD agenda based on the goals and desired results/ outcomes, and report thereon using the prescribed format; and
(d) use the HGDG tool to properly identify the gender issues on LGU PPAs or its portion that can be attributed to GAD activities.
